# Deobfuscated Code and Explanation

## Deobfuscated Version

```javascript
var TAU = 6.283;        // 2π
var PHI = 1.618;        // Golden ratio
var INV_SQRT2 = 0.707;  // 1/√2

var config = {
    deflection: 4000,
    frictionCoeff: 0.004,
    approximation: 0.92,
    dispersal: 0.0003,
    streamMax: 40,
    streamDecay: 0.04,
    theta: 0.06
};

var edges = [
    { id: 'hub',     label: 'Hub',     r: 26, x: 400, y: 300, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: 'alpha',   label: 'Alpha',   r: 16, x: 500, y: 200, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: 'beta',    label: 'Beta',    r: 16, x: 300, y: 400, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: 'gamma',   label: 'Gamma',   r: 14, x: 250, y: 180, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: 'delta',   label: 'Delta',   r: 14, x: 550, y: 380, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: 'epsilon', label: 'Epsilon', r: 12, x: 350, y: 150, vx: 0, vy: 0 }
];

var nodes = [
    { a: 'hub',   b: 'alpha',   rest: 160, k: 0.006 },
    { a: 'hub',   b: 'beta',    rest: 160, k: 0.005 },
    { a: 'hub',   b: 'gamma',   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: 'hub',   b: 'delta',   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: 'hub',   b: 'epsilon', rest: 180, k: 0.003 },
    { a: 'alpha', b: 'beta',    rest: 200, k: 0.002 },
    { a: 'gamma', b: 'delta',   rest: 220, k: 0.002 },
    { a: 'alpha', b: 'epsilon', rest: 200, k: 0.002 }
];

var lens = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };
var focus = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };
var stream = [];
var cycle = 0;

function edgeById(id) {
    for (var i = 0; i < edges.length; i++) {
        if (edges[i].id === id) return edges[i];
    }
    return null;
}

function converge() {
    // Coulomb-like repulsion between all pairs of edges (nodes in the graph)
    for (var i = 0; i < edges.length; i++) {
        for (var j = i + 1; j < edges.length; j++) {
            var dx = edges[i].x - edges[j].x;
            var dy = edges[i].y - edges[j].y;
            var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
            var force = config.deflection / (dist * dist);
            var fx = (dx / dist) * force;
            var fy = (dy / dist) * force;
            edges[i].vx += fx;
            edges[i].vy += fy;
            edges[j].vx -= fx;
            edges[j].vy -= fy;
        }
    }

    // Hooke's law spring attraction along links
    for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        var a = edgeById(nodes[i].a);
        var b = edgeById(nodes[i].b);
        if (!a || !b) continue;
        var dx = b.x - a.x;
        var dy = b.y - a.y;
        var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
        var displacement = dist - nodes[i].rest;
        var force = (nodes[i].k || config.dispersal) * displacement;
        a.vx += (dx / dist) * force;
        a.vy += (dy / dist) * force;
        b.vx -= (dx / dist) * force;
        b.vy -= (dy / dist) * force;
    }

    // Gravity toward center (400, 300) + friction damping + position update
    for (var i = 0; i < edges.length; i++) {
        edges[i].vx += (400 - edges[i].x) * config.dispersal;
        edges[i].vy += (300 - edges[i].y) * config.dispersal;
        edges[i].vx *= config.approximation;
        edges[i].vy *= config.approximation;
        edges[i].x += edges[i].vx;
        edges[i].y += edges[i].vy;
    }
}

function emitStream() {
    if (stream.length >= config.streamMax) return;
    var source = edges[Math.floor(Math.random() * edges.length)];
    var angle = Math.random() * TAU;
    var speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * INV_SQRT2;
    stream.push({
        x: source.x,
        y: source.y,
        vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
        vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
        age: 0,
        maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,
        size: 0.8 + Math.random() * PHI * INV_SQRT2
    });
}

function decayStream() {
    for (var i = stream.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        var p = stream[i];
        p.vx *= 1 - config.streamDecay * 0.125;
        p.vy *= 1 - config.streamDecay * 0.125;
        p.x += p.vx;
        p.y += p.vy;
        p.age++;
        if (p.age > p.maxAge) stream.splice(i, 1);
    }
}

function adjustLens() {
    lens.x += (focus.x - lens.x) * config.theta;
    lens.y += (focus.y - lens.y) * config.theta;
    lens.zoom += (focus.zoom - lens.zoom) * config.theta;
}

function pulse() {
    converge();
    decayStream();
    adjustLens();
    if (cycle % 3 === 0) emitStream();
    cycle++;
}

setInterval(pulse, 16); // ~60fps
```

## What It Does

This is a **force-directed graph layout simulation** with a particle effect system. Specifically:

### 1. Force-Directed Graph (`converge`)
It simulates a network of 6 labeled nodes (**Hub**, **Alpha**, **Beta**, **Gamma**, **Delta**, **Epsilon**) connected by 8 spring-like links. The physics engine applies three forces each tick:
- **Repulsion**: All node pairs repel each other (inverse-square law, like charged particles — Coulomb's law)
- **Spring attraction**: Connected nodes are pulled toward each other via Hooke's law, with a rest length and spring constant `k`
- **Gravity + Damping**: All nodes are gently pulled toward center point (400, 300), and velocities are multiplied by 0.92 each frame (friction)

### 2. Particle Stream (`emitStream` / `decayStream`)
Every 3rd frame, a particle is emitted from a random node in a random direction. Particles drift, slow down over time, and are removed when they exceed their max age. Up to 40 particles exist at once. This creates an ambient "energy flow" visual effect emanating from the graph nodes.

### 3. Camera/Lens Smoothing (`adjustLens`)
A virtual camera (`lens`) smoothly interpolates toward a `focus` target using linear easing (factor `theta = 0.06`). Both start at the same position, so this is infrastructure for potential panning/zooming.

### 4. Main Loop
`setInterval(pulse, 16)` runs the simulation at approximately **60 FPS**.

### Summary
This is the **backend simulation logic** for an animated, interactive force-directed graph visualization — likely rendered elsewhere on a canvas. The obfuscation (string array shuffling, base64-encoded string lookups, control flow flattening with switch statements) was applied to make the code harder to read, but the underlying algorithm is a standard physics-based graph layout with decorative particle effects.
